#### text ####
text:

After an hour train ride back to Ueno, we went to Ameyoko (飴横) for dinner. It's a lively, pedestrian (and bike) friendly outdoor shopping district with restaurants. James had looked up a delicious tonkatsu place, but when we went to Yamabe Okachimachi it had more of a line than our mountain-climbing legs wanted to wait through. We searched for a nearby tonkatsu place and found Tonkatsu Yamabe - which was the original branch of the same mini-chain!
It was the best tonkatsu I've had in my life.
