#### text ####
text: It had a lot of detailed and accessible information about the history of salt production around the world and in Japan. Because Japan has neither rock salt nor salt flats, they had to concentrate sea water and boil it to get salt. The museum walked us through the different innovations in seawater concentration and evaporation technology including what is used today.
